playerEntryList.name: James Harden
playerEntryList.analysis: James Harden is one of the top overall plays on the slate tonight in a great matchup against the Wizards. Harden stepped up last night for Houston who were without PG Chris Paul; going off for 40 points and 13 assists in 44 minutes on the floor. Harden should feast on a Washington defense that ranks 28th DvP against opposing guards.

playerEntryList.name: Jrue Holiday
playerEntryList.analysis: Jrue Holiday has been a model of consistency for the Pelicans this season and is a great cash game option tonight. Holiday has posted zero "dud" games this season with an 80% consistency rating.

playerEntryList.name: Clint Capela
playerEntryList.analysis: Clint Capela has been excellent over the last few weeks for the Rockets and is in a great spot tonight in a matchup against the Wizards. Capela's usage rate has shot up to 37% over Houston's last 5 games, putting Capela in cash game consideration at his price point.

playerEntryList.name: Nikola Vucevic
playerEntryList.analysis: Nikola Vucevic has flashed huge upside this season and is in a great spot tonight against the Warriors who will still be without Draymond Green. Vucevic has been dominate when playing on the road this season, posting a +/- of + 7.1.

playerEntryList.name: Bradley Beal
playerEntryList.analysis: Bradley Beal is a great option at SG at his price point. He is in a great spot tonight against the Rockets who have been an average team at defending opposing shooting guards. Beal leads the Wizards is usage over the last 5 games at 36.8%.

playerEntryList.name: Jeremy Lamb
playerEntryList.analysis: Jeremy Lamb has been consistently exceeding his salary expectations and he is a top mid-range value tonight in a matchup against the Bucks that has the highest total on the slate at 234 points. Lamb is 2nd on the team in usage rate over the past 5 games at 32.4%.

playerEntryList.name: Quinn Cook
playerEntryList.analysis: Quinn Cook has been decent for the Warriors since sliding into the starting lineup and is a good value option tonight against the Magic. Cook has posted a +/- of +4.3 in his 6 starts this season.
